# Development Workflow

## Feature sequence (do not skip)

1. **Plan** — planner agent: task spec with scope, files, acceptance criteria
2. **Implement** — one small task; follow `simple-code.mdc`
3. **Test** — testing-agent: run tests, add missing coverage
4. **Review** — code-review agent on the diff
5. **Document** — documentation agent if APIs, boundaries, or ADRs changed

## Task spec template

Create `docs/tasks/YYYYMMDD-short-name.md`:

```markdown
## Goal
## Repo(s)
## Acceptance criteria
## Files to touch
## Out of scope
## Contract changes (if any)
```

## When to invoke agents

| Situation | Agent |
|-----------|-------|
| New feature | planner |
| Cross-repo or boundary change | architect |
| Code written | testing-agent |
| Tests green | code-review |
| Architecture/API change | documentation |
| Code too complex | refactor |

## Commits and PRs

- One task per PR
- PR title: `[repo] short description`
- Link task spec in PR body

## No coding without plan

Features > 1 file or touching API contracts require a task spec first.
